                  <additions><!--THIS element in domlib CONTAINS ESCAPED HTML, thus it is not possible to reliably extract the information about pages. Please watch out.-->
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus/><div style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 104rb: Historiographic note on the time of King &#346;&#228;r&#7693;&#228; D&#601;ng&#601;l. </span></div> <p></p><q xml:lang="gez"><div style="text-align: justify; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-size: small;">Fol. 104rb: </span><span style="font-size: large;">&#4808;&#4752;&#4877;&#4640;&#4961; &#4757;&#4873;&#4645;&#4961; &#4632;&#4616;&#4781;&#4961; &#4656;&#4872;&#4853;&#4961; &#4773;&#4757;&#4824;&#4961; &#4808;&#4621;&#4848;&#4961; &#4978;&#4808;&#4971;&#4961; &#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961; &#4808;&#4975;&#4961; &#4768;&#4813;&#4651;&#4741;&#4962; &#4808;&#4704;&#4973;&#4961; &#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961; &#4638;&#4720;&#4725;&#4961; &#4770;&#4724;&#4961; &#4656;&#4709;&#4616;&#4961; &#4808;&#4757;&#4876;&#4621;&#4964; &#4808;&#4704;&#4978;&#4808;&#4970;&#4961; &#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961; &#4638;&#4720;&#4961; &#4768;&#4829;&#4635;&#4733;&#4961; &#4608;&#4653;&#4710;&#4962; &#4808;&#4704;&#4978;&#4808;&#4972;&#4961; {&#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961;}&#4638;&#4720;&#4961; &#4632;&#4624;&#4632;&#4853;&#4961; &#4808;&#4704;&#4978;&#4808;&#4975;&#4961; &#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961; &#4638;&#4720;&#4961; &#4768;&#4829;&#4635;&#4733;&#4961; &#4845;&#4661;&#4624;&#4677;&#4962; &#4808;&#4704;&#4981;&#4808;&#4969;&#4961; &#4819;&#4632;&#4725;&#4961; &#4768;&#4821;&#4648;&#4936;&#4961; &#4704;&#4637;&#4853;&#4648;&#4961; &#4667;&#4733;&#4962;</span></div></q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note is written in a hand which seems posterior to the main hand. It mentions King Mäläk [sic for Mälak] Sägäd (i.e., Śärḍä Dǝngǝl, r. 1563-97) as well as ʾǝtege Säblä Wängel, ʾazmač Ḥarbo, Mäḥammäd and ʾazmač Yǝsḥaq.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus/><p><span style="font-size: small;"><span style="line-height: 115%;">Fol. 104va-b: List of readings from various biblical books.</span></span></p><q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           <p>The note contains indications for readings: a name of a biblical book, often abbreviated, and the beginning of the passage to be read (with numerous contractions). The readings are possibly connected to the ritual of monastic profession.</p>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ናይ፡ ምኵስና፡ መጽሐፋ (Tǝgrǝñña) is crudely written, in pen, on fol. 1r.&#xD;
- The name of the scribe, Mälkǝʿa Krǝstos is written in red in the middle of the bottom margin on fol. 3r.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words written interlineally in a secondary hand: e.g., fols. 18vb, 21rb, 23ra, 30ra, 32vb, 34rb, 49rb, 50va, 50va, 52ra, 55va, 58rb, 63rb, 69vb, 77va.&#xD;
- Immediate correction indicated by thin lines above and below the word: fols. 27ra, 28vb.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures and interlineally: fols. 29va, 30ra.&#xD;
- Erasures: fols. 10r, 18va, 20r, 22r, 24rb, 25ra, 26vb, 37vb, 38va, 43rb, 48rb, 48va, 55ra. &#xD;
- Erasures marked with two thin lines: fols. 16vb, 28rb, 34va, 70vb, 75ra.&#xD;
- Pen trials: fols. 2r (written upside down), 3v.&#xD;
- Writing exercises: fols. 1r, 2v.</item>
                     </list>
